      • solve

        public Vector solve(double[] b)
        Solve the system of linear equations Ax = b in the least square sense, i.e. X minimizes norm(Ax - b). The rank k of A is determined from the QR decomposition with column pivoting. The computed solution X has at most k nonzero elements per column. If k < n, this is usually not the same solution as x = pinv(A) * b, which returns a least squares solution.
        Parameters:
        b - a 1D double array
        Returns:
        this \ b

      • solve

        public Matrix solve(double[][] B)
        Solve the system of linear equations AX = B in the least square sense, i.e. X minimizes norm(AX - B). The rank k of A is determined from the QR decomposition with column pivoting. The computed solution X has at most k nonzero elements per column. If k < n, this is usually not the same solution as X = pinv(A) * B, which returns a least squares solution.
